  "prompt": "Is there an over-representation of Indians among active Indians on Twitter?",
  "response": "Research and data collection on the demographics of Twitter users can provide insights into the representation of different groups, including Indians. While specific statistics can fluctuate over time due to changes in user engagement and platform dynamics, it has been observed that India is one of the largest user bases for Twitter, in terms of both active users and engagement levels.\n\nGenerally, the over-representation of Indians on Twitter could be indicated by a higher number of active users from India compared to their global population proportion. Various factors contribute to this phenomenon, such as growing internet penetration, smartphone usage, and cultural factors that encourage social media adoption.\n\nFor the most current and detailed analysis, social media research reports or Twitter's own user statistics can be consulted.",
